### Merge Sort Insight

While merging:

```text
Left Half
Right Half
```

If:

```python
left[i] > right[j]
```

Then every remaining element in left half forms inversion.

Count:

```python
mid - i + 1
```

---

### Optimal Code

```python
def merge(arr, low, mid, high):

    temp = []

    left = low
    right = mid + 1

    count = 0

    while left <= mid and right <= high:

        if arr[left] <= arr[right]:

            temp.append(arr[left])
            left += 1

        else:

            temp.append(arr[right])

            count += (mid - left + 1)

            right += 1

    while left <= mid:
        temp.append(arr[left])
        left += 1

    while right <= high:
        temp.append(arr[right])
        right += 1

    for i in range(low, high+1):
        arr[i] = temp[i-low]

    return count
```

#### Complexity

```text
Time  : O(n log n)
Space : O(n)
```

#### Learning

* Merge Sort Application
* Counting Pairs
* Divide and Conquer

